As of: 2019-06-28

General hints about the file types in LTspice:

.asc  Schematic files
.asy  Symbol files
.plt  Plot settings files 
.net  LTspice netlist
.raw  Raw data output file
.fft  Result file from a FFT
.sub  Subcircuit or model definition file
Any other extension is allowed,
e.g. .mod, .lib, .abc, .xyz, .cir
These files are often added with the ".include" or ".lib"
SPICE command.
.cir  General SPICE netlist file

Files > Filter

Filter: Analog & IIR (with interpolation/decimation): -3dB/oct, Bessel, Butterworth, Chebyshev I & II, Cauer/Elliptic. FIR (with interpolation/decimation): frequency sampling, Dolph-Chebyshev, Kaiser, Blackman, Hamming, Hann, Bartlett, Tuckey, Lanczos, moving average, pulse shaping(Gaussian, raised+root-raised cosine), differentiator, Hilbert transformer, half-band, and more. "Filter.zip" is the manual -- it has the library (filter.sub) and the symbol (Filter.asy) inside.
EMC Filter: EMC Filter supply simulation approch
Time_Domain_Filtering: Time Domain Filtering using Delay or "Z-1"
Laplace_eq.asc: Laplace transfer function of degree >2, made with LTspice primitives.
Allpass_2nd_order.asc: Passive 2nd Order All-Pass
Bluetooth1.asc: This cockraft-walton voltage multiplier circuit. I am expecting the input voltage to increase 8 times corresponding to stages. This circuit must be simulated in CMOS 0.25u technology, but I am nt able to run the circuit in this platform.
RC.zip: Study of decoupling an ICC VCC pin and effects of source resistance.
fit z 1 no extra lr.xls: spreadsheet to fit LRC impedance to data
compare laplace and lpf q=1.asc: comparing an LCR lowpass with a Laplace source
RLC Biquad Current Sourced.asc: Current Sourced RLC Biquad Circuit Realization
RLC Biquad.asc: A Simpler RLC Biquad Filter
LPF4P4I.zip: Four integrator implementation of Butterworth LPF.
Integrator Study LTSpice.zip: A Study of Two Integration Subcircuits
synth higher order Ls 4pole Bess.asc: Generalizing the structure of kbiquad2g (in dual form) to higher orders. This example shows a 4th order Bessel filter; the polynomial coefficients are derived using the recurrence relation I posted in an early mail on the 'Bessel poles' thread.
biqLTSPICE 0.3.exe: Program for creating .param blocks for the kbiquad2g demo. Does lowpass Butterworth and Chebychev. Might be some precision issues at high order. Creates some comment lines to paste into the component arguments too, to save time.
kbiquad2g.asy: kbiquad2g 2nd order biquad component symbol
kbiquad2g.asc: kbiquad2g 2nd order biquad component schematic
demonstrate cascade filter using LRC biquad component.asc: shows the use of the kbiquad2g 2nd order biquad component with values assigned in a .param statement

Files > FAQ > Bugs and Features

Interpretation of Pulse parameters have changed.: Convention dictates that source value be left at the last instance of change....
Rpar is not implemented for inductors with Equations: OP had to put an external Rpar to stop oscillations...
No k for inductors with equations: Inductors with equation should be capable of being coupled.
Default models must work.....: Default models for Diodes, BJTs, MOS should work in any analysis, out of the box...
Options into Log file...: When requested all options in use will be put into log file...
FFT plots: Long standing request for stick plots in FFT
Adding Plot Panes: Sometimes more convenient to add them on the bottom..
Re: Special characters and spaces in schematic names: Help to be expanded about special characters in lower level hierarchy files.
Amp.Second v. Coulomb: No ability to arbitrarily re-label X and Y axis in plots.
BOM seems to be broke: Netlist is ok; But, BOM fails
Trapz Integration rings.....: Trapz integration produces bogus ringing...
Caps and Inductors Initial Conditons: Caps and Inductors differ in IC specifications.
Archival Feature: Request for Single Folder archival feature
Better IGBT model: Spiceman's request for better IGBT model....
Bugs and Requests : Bugs and Request Message which started this..
Multi-Core operation...: Create an example and more detailed help info to explain multi-core..
Parameter extraction...: Explicit Model parameter explanation or a companion Model extraction program.
Trise,Tfall or Rout or Tau for A-devices: Choose one of those three!!!
-frequencies on Xaxis: Change Xaxis to include -ve frequencies
Format for "K" is stricter: The coupling factor for inductors doesn't allow "=""
_ve time and -ve frequencies: Is there a way to change the time or frequency axis to include -ve values?

Files > Lib > Math_blocks- Filter-Power

Pwr.zip: (3-phase related unless specified: 3-level PWM modulator, voltage-/current-mode switching full-bridges, generator/load w/out harmonics, 3-to-3 timed relay, Clarke, Park and inverse matrices, abc/dq0 and inverse, hysteresis full-bridge comparator (1-phase), voltage/current sensors, [thyristor/diode] bridge rectifier, RLC series/parallel load, wattmeter, disturbance,phase angle generator,cable model, SVPWM,SVHCC)
Math.zip: (many mathematical functions already existent in LTspice plus some home-brew, but under a more stream-lined form)
Filt.zip: (AGC, dead-time, dead-zone, delay, differentiator, frequency detector, [voltage controlled or static] lead-lag, FFT, gain, [resettable] integrator, limiter, analog MUX, universal PID (analog+digital), PLL, state-space). The universal filter is in Files/Filter/Filter/.
0101.zip: (binary <--> decimal, 16bit ADC, 16bit DAC, 16bit asynchronous counter , JK Flip-Flop)
script.zip: This is a script (*nix, but it may work elsewhere with the proper environments) for searching in the schematics and making the replacements from the old Math/Filt/Pwr to the new ones. Changes have to be made according to each and everyone's needs.
